# MongoDB Atlas Connection String
# Replace with your actual MongoDB Atlas credentials
# Format: mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/database_name
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://your-username:your-password@your-cluster.mongodb.net/devoirs2026?retryWrites=true&w=majority

# How to get your connection string:
# 1. Go to MongoDB Atlas Dashboard: https://cloud.mongodb.com/
# 2. Click on "Connect" for your cluster
# 3. Choose "Connect your application"
# 4. Copy the connection string
# 5. Replace <username>, <password>, and <dbname> with your values
# 6. If password contains special characters (@, :, /, etc.), URL encode them:
#    @ → %40
#    : → %3A
#    / → %2F
#    + → %2B
#    % → %25
#    etc.

# For Vercel deployment:
# - DO NOT commit this file with real values
# - Add MONGODB_URI in Vercel Dashboard → Settings → Environment Variables
# - Add it for all environments (Production, Preview, Development)

# For local development:
# 1. Copy this file to .env
# 2. Replace with your real values
# 3. The .env file is in .gitignore and won't be committed
